item.description:
@krackkid wrote:

On the forums it said people haven’t changed there password from 2.24 and stuff so thats why there getting hacked.

and yeah I just use “test” with the password of “blank”.

wired420 View Profile View Forum Posts Private Message Join Date:Aug 2010 Posts:50 I've personally looked through the UID code. Its just stores the information from inside the accounts menu in RSBot. If you don't give RSBot your password or pin all thats in this file is a default account blank place holder. If you remove your accounts from the bot, and delete this file you'll see it only comes back with the default info. This info is required so that the GUI realizes its the right file its reading from.

No where have I seen anything where this is used maliciously in 2.25, and yes. I’ve actually been through most of the files.

Edit: Yes there was code in previous versions that used this to steal your passwords. So if you haven’t changed your password, and your far down the list, Gh0$t just hasn’t gotten to your account yet.

Change your password and delete any Pre 2.25 versions you have.
